                                         JOHANNESBURG - United States police have arrested an Indian man after a woman accused him of sexually assaulting her as she slept beside him on a US flight. Officials say the 34-year-old man was sitting between his wife and the alleged victim when the incident happened. According to media reports, the woman says she had woken up to find her shirt and trousers unbuttoned and the suspect's hands in her trousers. The suspect has denied these claims, saying he had been in deep sleep during the flight and did not know where he had placed his hands.